{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Plan-review advisory dispositions (17 findings, review @5a39f85eb PASS):\n\nACCEPTED (reflected in plan/tests/impl):\n- #1 & #4 (0.54, dup): fsck_recover gate must NOT block --detect-only (read-only diagnostic). ACCEPT — gate only the mutating path (skip when detect_only). Reflected: held-out test invokes fsck-recover WITHOUT --detect-only; impl skips gate for detect-only.\n- #3 (0.54): init/MCP-boot entry points need StoreIncompatibleError->non-zero conversion, not just init.py ensure unit. ACCEPT — already added via the run_ensures re-raise remediation (brief §6b); init/mcp-boot surface it as non-zero exit.\n- #5 (0.26): describe_store_compat -> dict|None named export for fsck diagnostic/AC6. ACCEPT — defined as {kind,detail} dict in remediation.\n- #7 (0.26): jq -e '.compat_error.kind' matches any string. ACCEPT — held-out test asserts exact value (.compat_error.kind == \"unknown_format_version\"), stronger than presence.\n- #9 (0.26): more write_lock() callers exist than enumerated. ACCEPT (informational) — the single gate inside lock.acquire() covers ALL of them by construction; coverage-lint test greps for competing acquire()/write_lock() definitions.\n- #10 (0.0): _version.py format_version/SCHEMA_VERSION note. ACCEPT — comment-only clarification.\n- #11 (0.0): run_ensures \"Never raises\" docstring now inaccurate. ACCEPT — update docstring to note it raises StoreIncompatibleError (fail-closed).\n\nREJECTED (with rationale):\n- #2 (0.4): vague \"AC/DoD quality\" — REJECT, ACs are already concrete + test-backed.\n- #6 (0.26): git-stash vs monkeypatch rollback-proof mismatch — REJECT, rollback safety is that a pre-v1.0 binary ignores the unknown file; documented in docs/migrations.md, no code change warranted.\n- #8 (0.26): what is logged on a healthy no-op check — REJECT, a compatible/absent record is a silent no-op by design.\n- #12 (0.0): TOCTOU (record read before fcntl) — REJECT, the record is written only by the ensure unit under the same lock and is effectively immutable at runtime; a fail-closed safety check, not a serialization point; the next write re-checks.\n- #13 (0.0): no AC for format_version/SCHEMA_VERSION relationship — REJECT, covered by the _version.py comment.\n- #14 (0.0): permission-denied corrupt sub-case untested — REJECT the test (chmod-based perm tests are flaky / root-bypassed) but ACCEPT the code path: check_store_compat maps OSError -> StoreIncompatibleError.\n- #15 & #16 (0.0): reconcile.py:133/670 citation is a param line, not the tracker path — REJECT as a citation nitpick; implementation uses repo_root/\".tickets-tracker\" correctly regardless.\n- #17 (0.0): docs/releasing.md omitted — REJECT for this leaf; the store-compat record is a migrations concern (docs/migrations.md); releasing.md is owned by the release stories F1/F3/F4."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784093300210607001,"uuid":"185e890e-fe66-45a8-9e90-61f7aa30c28b"}